expansion.name_gatherer: Duel Decks: Mirrodin Pure vs. New Phyrexia

cards.name: Platinum Angel
cards.text:
Flying
You can't lose the game and your opponents can't win the game.
cards.flavor: She is the apex of the artificer's craft, the spirit of the divine called out of base metal.

cards.name: Memnite
cards.flavor: Reminders of Memnarch's reign still skirr across Mirrodin, reminiscent of his form if not his power.

cards.name: Steel Wall
cards.text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)
cards.flavor:
"We sculpt the land into what we need-homes, armament, fortresses of war. Our strength comes not only from knowing, but from commanding the terrain."
-Raksha Golden Cub, leonin kha

cards.name: Ardent Recruit
cards.text: Metalcraft - Ardent Recruit gets +2/+2 as long as you control three or more artifacts.
cards.flavor: "We lost our homes and our kin. We won't let those rotters take our future as well."

cards.name: Vedalken Certarch
cards.text: Metalcraft - {T}: Tap target artifact, creature, or land. Activate only if you control three or more artifacts.
cards.flavor: "An appropriately detailed model is indistinguishable from reality, and much easier to control."

cards.name: Gold Myr
cards.text: {T}: Add {W}.

cards.name: Myr Retriever
cards.text: When Myr Retriever dies, return another target artifact card from your graveyard to your hand.
cards.flavor: Mephidross gives up treasure easily … as long as you take its place.

cards.name: Silver Myr
cards.text: {T}: Add {U}.
cards.flavor: The myr are like quicksilver: malleable in function and adaptable in form.

cards.name: Trinket Mage
cards.text: When Trinket Mage enters the battlefield, you may search your library for an artifact card with mana value 1 or less, reveal that card, put it into your hand, then shuffle.

cards.name: Grand Architect
cards.text:
Other blue creatures you control get +1/+1.
{U}: Target artifact creature becomes blue until end of turn.
Tap an untapped blue creature you control: Add {C}{C}. Spend this mana only to cast artifact spells or activate abilities of artifacts.

cards.name: Silent Arbiter
cards.text:
No more than one creature can attack each combat.
No more than one creature can block each combat.
cards.flavor: Scholars say that arbiters exist on every world, created by an unknown hand to enforce justice.

cards.name: Glimmerpoint Stag
cards.text:
Vigilance
When Glimmerpoint Stag enters the battlefield, exile another target permanent. Return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of the next end step.

cards.name: Argent Sphinx
cards.text:
Flying
Metalcraft - {U}: Exile Argent Sphinx. Return it to the battlefield under your control at the beginning of the next end step. Activate only if you control three or more artifacts.
cards.flavor: A great mirage, a dream of wings and silver.

cards.name: Kuldotha Forgemaster
cards.text: {T}, Sacrifice three artifacts: Search your library for an artifact card, put it onto the battlefield, then shuffle.
cards.flavor: The goblins say it used to be larger, before it began to stoke the Great Furnace with pieces of itself.

cards.name: Spire Serpent
cards.text:
Defender
Metalcraft - As long as you control three or more artifacts, Spire Serpent gets +2/+2 and can attack as though it didn't have defender.
cards.flavor: A mirror to draw its eye, a rod to rouse its rage, and a sword to break its bonds.

cards.name: Darksteel Sentinel
cards.text:
Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)
Vigilance
Indestructible (Damage and effects that say "destroy" don't destroy this creature. If its toughness is 0 or less, it's still put into its owner's graveyard.)

cards.name: Duplicant
cards.text:
Imprint - When Duplicant enters the battlefield, you may exile target nontoken creature.
As long as a card exiled with Duplicant is a creature card, Duplicant has the power, toughness, and creature types of the last creature card exiled with Duplicant. It's still a Shapeshifter.

cards.name: Lumengrid Gargoyle
cards.text: Flying
cards.flavor:
"Anything that watches without sleep and fights without fear is a valuable ally against the Phyrexians."
-Kara Vrist, Neurok agent

cards.name: Darksteel Gargoyle
cards.text:
Flying
Indestructible (Damage and effects that say "destroy" don't destroy this creature.)
cards.flavor: The ultimate treasure is one that guards itself.

cards.name: Condemn
cards.text: Put target attacking creature on the bottom of its owner's library. Its controller gains life equal to its toughness.

cards.name: Dispatch
cards.text:
Tap target creature.
Metalcraft - If you control three or more artifacts, exile that creature.
cards.flavor: Venser wondered if it could still be called a teleportation spell if the destination is oblivion.

cards.name: Steelshaper's Gift
cards.text: Search your library for an Equipment card, reveal that card, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
cards.flavor: Some blades seek their own wielders.

cards.name: Neurok Stealthsuit
cards.text:
Equipped creature has shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
{U}{U}: Attach Neurok Stealthsuit to target creature you control.
Equip {1} ({1}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

cards.name: Talisman of Progress
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}: Add {W} or {U}. Talisman of Progress deals 1 damage to you.

cards.name: Viridian Claw

Equipped creature gets +1/+0 and has first strike.
Equip {1}
cards.flavor: "Phyrexians can't corrupt what they can't get close enough to touch."

cards.name: Purge
cards.text: Destroy target artifact creature or black creature. It can't be regenerated.
cards.flavor: For the first and last time, the horrific creature experienced terror.

cards.name: Test of Faith
cards.text: Prevent the next 3 damage that would be dealt to target creature this turn. For each 1 damage prevented this way, put a +1/+1 counter on that creature.
cards.flavor: Those who survive the test bear a mark of power anyone can recognize.

cards.name: Turn the Tide
cards.text: Creatures your opponents control get -2/-0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"Let their mindless armies come and face the might of genius."
-Varil, Neurok partisan

cards.name: Thunderstaff
cards.text:
As long as Thunderstaff is untapped, if a creature would deal combat damage to you, prevent 1 of that damage.
{2}, {T}: Attacking creatures get +1/+0 until end of turn.

cards.name: Arrest
cards.text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature can't attack or block, and its activated abilities can't be activated.
cards.flavor: Bladehold houses a rogues' gallery filled with the living "statues" of the worst enemies of the Auriok.

cards.name: Thirst for Knowledge
cards.text: Draw three cards. Then discard two cards unless you discard an artifact card.
cards.flavor: Lymph, the fluid essence of blinkmoths, is prized by wizards for the rush of intellect it provides.

cards.name: Stoic Rebuttal
cards.text:
Metalcraft - This spell costs {1} less to cast if you control three or more artifacts.
Counter target spell.
cards.flavor: Obsessed with the pursuit of knowledge above all else, vedalken can appear to be cold and emotionless.

cards.name: White Sun's Zenith
cards.text: Create X 2/2 white Cat creature tokens. Shuffle White Sun's Zenith into its owner's library.
cards.flavor: After the Battle of Liet Field, the white sun crested above Taj-Nar, bringing hope to all who survived the carnage.

cards.name: Ancient Den
cards.text: {T}: Add {W}.
cards.flavor: Taj-Nar, throne of Raksha Golden Cub, destined leader of the leonin prides.

cards.name: Blinkmoth Nexus
cards.text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}: Blinkmoth Nexus becomes a 1/1 Blinkmoth artifact creature with flying until end of turn. It's still a land.
{1}, {T}: Target Blinkmoth creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.

cards.name: Coastal Tower
cards.text:
Coastal Tower enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {W} or {U}.
cards.flavor: A beacon in the night, a dream in the fog.

cards.name: Forbidding Watchtower
cards.text:
Forbidding Watchtower enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {W}.
{1}{W}: Forbidding Watchtower becomes a 1/5 white Soldier creature until end of turn. It's still a land.

cards.name: Seat of the Synod
cards.text: {T}: Add {U}.

cards.name: Terramorphic Expanse
cards.text: {T}, Sacrifice Terramorphic Expanse: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

cards.name: Phyrexian Plaguelord

{T}, Sacrifice Phyrexian Plaguelord: Target creature gets -4/-4 until end of turn.
Sacrifice a creature: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"The final stage of the illness: delirium, convulsions, and death."
-Phyrexian progress notes

cards.name: Fume Spitter
cards.text: Sacrifice Fume Spitter: Put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.
cards.flavor:
"Our archers made sport of it as it fumbled its way up the slag ridge. As it collapsed we thought ourselves safe, but the foul thing carried more than necrogen."
-Adaran, Tangle hunter

cards.name: Myr Sire
cards.text: When Myr Sire dies, create a 1/1 colorless Phyrexian Myr artifact creature token.
cards.flavor: For the Phyrexians, death is not an end, nor a one-time occurrence.

cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
{T}: Add {C}.
cards.flavor: They watch for a new master, one more sinister than the last.

cards.name: Viridian Emissary
cards.text: When Viridian Emissary dies, you may search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

cards.name: Phyrexian Ghoul
cards.text: Sacrifice a creature: Phyrexian Ghoul gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Phyrexia wastes nothing. Its food chain is a spiraling cycle.

cards.name: Rot Wolf
cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
Whenever a creature dealt damage by Rot Wolf this turn dies, you may draw a card.

Wither (This deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters.)
Whenever a creature an opponent controls with a -1/-1 counter on it dies, you may return that card to the battlefield under your control.

cards.name: Viridian Corrupter
cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)

cards.text:
Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)
Whenever a player casts a spell, sacrifice a creature.

Flying
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)

cards.name: Soul Snuffers
cards.text: When Soul Snuffers enters the battlefield, put a -1/-1 counter on each creature.
cards.flavor: They once sought to unite with the flame of transcendence. Now they seek only to extinguish the lights of others.

cards.name: Mitotic Slime

cards.name: Plaguemaw Beast

cards.flavor: Phyrexia's spiral of consumption grows ever wider and darker.

cards.name: Phyrexian Juggernaut
cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
Phyrexian Juggernaut attacks each combat if able.
cards.flavor: Where nature impedes, Phyrexians overcome.

cards.name: Drooling Groodion
cards.text: {2}{B}{G}, Sacrifice a creature: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Another target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.

cards.flavor:
"Meat and eggs. We eat!"
-Borborygmos

cards.name: Innocent Blood

cards.flavor: Zombies mourn for the living and celebrate those who will soon be given the gift of death.

cards.text:

{4}, {T}: Proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter of each kind already there.)

cards.name: Exhume

cards.flavor:
"Death-an outmoded concept. We sleep, and we change."
-Sitrik, birth priest

cards.name: Phyrexian Altar
cards.text: Sacrifice a creature: Add one mana of any color.
cards.flavor:
"Your life was meaningless, but your death will glorify Yawgmoth."
-Tsabo Tavoc

cards.name: Morbid Plunder
cards.text: Return up to two target creature cards from your graveyard to your hand.
cards.flavor: Even the dead are raw materials for the Phyrexian vision of perfection.

cards.name: Putrefy
cards.text: Destroy target artifact or creature. It can't be regenerated.
cards.flavor:
"All matter, animate or not, rots when exposed to time. We merely speed up the process."
-Ezoc, Golgari rot farmer

cards.name: Diabolic Servitude
cards.text:
When Diabolic Servitude enters the battlefield, return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
When the creature put onto the battlefield with Diabolic Servitude dies, exile it and return Diabolic Servitude to its owner's hand.
When Diabolic Servitude leaves the battlefield, exile the creature put onto the battlefield with Diabolic Servitude.

cards.name: Barter in Blood

cards.flavor:
"In the game of conquest, who cares about the pawns if the king yet reigns?"
-Geth, keeper of the Vault

cards.name: Reprocess

cards.flavor: Everything will find its use in Phyrexia. Eventually.

cards.name: Triumph of the Hordes

cards.name: Spread the Sickness
cards.text: Destroy target creature, then proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter of each kind already there.)
cards.flavor: Life is ephemeral. Phyrexia is eternal.
